      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change < 2% between successive refinements; Richardson extrapolation-based GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the pedicle screw-rod construct. Von Mises stress at critical notch location and construct stiffness converged to within 1.3% between medium and fine meshes. GCI estimated at 3.1%. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals < 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear quasi-static analyses converged with force residuals below 1e-7 for all 11 construct configurations. Energy balance monitored throughout loading; maximum imbalance 0.04%. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments; documented peer review checklist completed.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by a second analyst not involved in original model construction. Boundary condition application, contact definitions, and material property assignments verified against ASTM F1717 test fixture specifications. Peer review checklist completed and archived. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening selected based on published titanium alloy characterization; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface slip.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity; material constants from published coupon test data. Augmented Lagrangian contact formulation applied at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces. Model form appropriate for quasi-static monotonic loading regime of ASTM F1717. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test specimens; material properties from tensile coupon testing of same lot material; friction coefficients from published tribology literature.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry digitized via coordinate measuring machine on representative specimens from the same manufacturing lot used in testing. Elastic modulus, yield strength, and tangent modulus from tensile coupon tests (n=5 per material). Friction coefficients assigned from Ti-Ti tribology literature (mu=0.2). Comprehensive Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed across all model inputs to characterize the distribution of predicted QoIs; 10,000 samples drawn from input distributions covering geometric tolerances, material property scatter, and friction variability. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N >= 10 experimental constructs from production-representative manufacturing lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design nominal.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA and DePuy Synthes). All specimens from same production lot; incoming dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to drawing tolerances. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at 95% confidence. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two load levels or fixture configurations to characterize condition sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 fixture configuration and loading rate. No variation in test angle, load rate, or environmental condition was explored. This limits characterization of model response across the condition space. Achieved level 1 is below required level 2; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 submissions at this device class."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs traceable to experimentally measured specimen-specific values; fixture geometry in FEA matches ASTM F1717 fixture dimensions within 0.1 mm.",
      "rationale": "Specimen-specific CMM measurements used to parameterize each of the 11 FEA models. ASTM F1717 fixture block geometry reproduced from engineering drawings; FEA fixture dimensions verified against physical fixture measurements within 0.05 mm. Input parameter equivalency between test and simulation confirmed. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; relative error < 10%.",
      "rationale": "Validation metric E/uval computed for construct stiffness (0.87), yield force (1.41), and force at 40 mm displacement (1.62); all below the 1.96 threshold. Relative errors of 4.2%, 6.8%, and 7.3% respectively, all within the 10% acceptance bound. Quantitative output comparison criterion satisfied for all QoIs. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinically and regulatorily relevant construct performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and FDA guidance.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three primary performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly characterize the mechanical behavior relevant to in vivo load transfer and fatigue initiation. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
